221;<\/em><\/p>\n<p>If the book isn&#8217;t enough, or if you want to participate, there&#8217;s also a <a href=\"http:\/\/www.flickr.com\/groups\/thoughtlessacts\/pool\/\">Flickr group<\/a> on the topic.  Here are some highlights:<br \/>\n<img src=\"http:\/\/static.flickr.com\/74\/161552291_5faee9aac4_t.jpg\" \/>&nbsp; <img src=\"http:\/\/static.flickr.com\/78\/158179416_dcd2d76ffa_t.jpg\" \/>&nbsp; <img src=\"http:\/\/static.flickr.com\/39\/84388864_2518d58d50_t.jpg\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&#8220;<font size=\"+1\">Problems worth solving&#8230;<\/font> It&#8217;s a mistake to interpret observations too literally, though: the world doesn&#8217;t need a uniquq design solution for every creative adaptationwe see (that&#8217;s the kind of stuff that ends up advertised in in-flight catalogs!)&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>The book has a very nice <a href=\"http:\/\/www.thoughtlessacts.com\/\">web site<\/a>, which cycles through a selection of photos from the book when you click on different sections; however, you the object itself is really very wonderful.  You should <a href=\"http:\/\/www.amazon.com\/exec\/obidos\/redirect?link_code=as2&amp;path=ASIN\/0811847756&amp;tag=ultrasaurus-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325\">buy it<\/a> or ask me to show it to you the next time you see me :)<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>How does our environment influence our behavior? This lovely book, by Jane Fulton Suri + IDEO, highlights things we do as we interact with the objects in our world and with other people. It challenges us to consider: which of these acts are conscious and which are done without thought? How do we react, respond,&hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2006\/07\/thoughtless-acts\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2006\/07\/thoughtless-acts\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":84,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"o